Body evenly oval, lateral margins evenly curved and continuous between pronotum and elytron (
Fig. 6
).

Coloration (
Fig. 6
). Head orange grading into diffuse, light yellow region medially on frons and testaceous to black mediad and posteriad of eyes, in some specimens extending anteriorly around eye to lateral margin of frons. Pronotum broadly black or testaceous medially along anterior and posterior margins, black regions meeting medially in lighter, testaceous transverse band; posterolateral margins of pronotum narrowly black, lateral surfaces yellow, extending medially to dark region; scutellum darkly colored, often black. Elytron testaceous, with narrow, lateral diffuse pale band and four variously developed yellow spots, one parascutellar most evident, one humeral least evident, one slightly posterior of middle near lateral margin, one anteapically. Appendages of head, legs and ventral surfaces, including elytral epipleuron, pale orange to reddish, somewhat darker on thoracic sterna and metacoxae; apical abdominal tergite yellow.

Male genitalia (
Fig. 11
). Median lobe broad, in left lateral view weakly curved, apex expanded, dorsal surface weakly sinuate, apex broadly rounded, covered in pores in apical 2/3; ventral groove in right lateral view strongly narrowed at half length, abruptly widened in apical 1/4.
